        "text": "Commercial stations such as [[Radio Normandie]] and Radio Luxembourg ([[Radio Luxembourg (English)]]) broadcast into the UK from other European countries. This provided a very popular alternative to the rather austere BBC. These stations were closed during the War, and only Radio Luxembourg returned afterward. BBC television broadcasts in Britain began on November 2, 1936, and continued until wartime ([[World War II]]) conditions closed the service ([[Service (economics)]]) in 1939."
